Raw Text:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 859
H.P. 545 House of Representatives, March 4, 2025
Resolve, Directing the Treasurer of State to Review and Develop
Options for Meeting the Banking Needs of the Cannabis Industry
Reference to the Committee on Veterans and Legal Affairs suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative CLUCHEY of Bowdoinham.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Banking and cannabis industry study. Resolved: That the Treasurer
2 of State shall, in consultation with the Finance Authority of Maine, the Department of
3 Administrative and Financial Services, Office of Cannabis Policy and any other state
4 agency or organization that the Treasurer of State determines to be appropriate, review
5 options for meeting the banking needs of individuals and businesses involved in the adult
6 use cannabis and medical cannabis industries in the State, including examining banking
7 solutions in other states that have legalized cannabis use, banking solution efforts under
8 way at the federal level and actions the Legislature can take to encourage federal action on
9 banking solutions.
10 Sec. 2. Report. Resolved: That, by December 3, 2025, the Treasurer of State shall
11 submit a report based on the review in section 1 to the Joint Standing Committee on
12 Veterans and Legal Affairs. The committee is authorized to submit legislation based on the
13 report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This resolve directs the Treasurer of State to review options for meeting the banking
1166 needs of individuals and businesses involved in the adult use cannabis and medical
1177 cannabis industries in the State, including examining banking solutions in other states that
1188 have legalized cannabis use, banking solution efforts under way at the federal level and
